Description: CVE-2026-5704 - Fix more -t/-x discrepancies
 A flaw in tar allows a remote attacker to craft a malicious archive
 leading to hidden file injection with fully attacker-controlled content
 that bypasses pre-extraction inspection mechanisms. The fix ensures
 consistent handling of member data between -t (list) and -x (extract)
 modes by always calling skip_member after extraction, tracking the
 skipped state in read_header, and removing the DIRTYPE exemption in
 skim_member that allowed directory data to be silently skipped during
 listing but processed during extraction.
Origin: upstream, https://git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/tar.git/commit/?id=b8d8a61b25588caca4efaf9bdd2e3f1a49da77e3
Author: Paul Eggert <eggert@cs.ucla.edu>
Last-Update: 2026-04-23

